-- Suez Unit May Bid for Wipro’s Water Division, Times Says
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2012-09-13T09:54:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-13/suez-unit-may-bid-for-wipro-s-water-division-times-says.html
A unit of Suez Environnement, the
second-biggest water utility, is one of three companies seeking
to buy the water-treatment business of  India ’s  Wipro Ltd. (WPRO) , the
Times of India  reported , citing people it didn’t identify.  Suez’s Degremont, New Delhi-based Earth Water Group and
Metito Ltd., based in Sharjah,  United Arab Emirates , are
preparing bids, according to the report.  Earth Water Group announced this week that it raised $15
million in funding for investments and possible acquisitions
from CLSA Capital Partners of  Singapore .  Previous customers of Wipro’s water unit include The Coca-
Cola Co. and  United Breweries Ltd. (UBBL) , according to the report.
Wipro, India’s third-largest software exporter, hired Anand
Rathi Financial Services Ltd. to find a buyer, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
